               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Rāʾǝya Yoḥannǝs "Revelation of John" [Rev. 1:9-16:19] (fols.
                     3ra-34vb), incomplete
 
 Additiones 1-2.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The correct order of the fols. would be as follows:</note>
                     <note>Rev. 1:9-2:6 (<locus from="33ra" to="34vb">33ra-34vb</locus>); Rev.
                        2:6-16:19 (<locus from="3ra" to="32vb">3ra-32vb</locus>).</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="Codex">
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                           <material key="parchment"/>
                        </support>
                        <extent>Made of <measure unit="leaf">34.0</measure> folios, of which
                              <measure unit="leaf" type="blank"/> blank <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 1vb, 2v., in <measure unit="quire"/> quires . <dimensions type="outer">
                              <height unit="mm">125</height>
                              <width unit="mm">125</width>
                              <depth unit="mm">30</depth>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        <foliation/>
                        <collation>
                           <list>
                              <item xml:id="q1">The quire structure cannot be identified due to the
                                 poor condition of the Ms.</item>
                           </list>
                        </collation>
                        <condition key="deficient">The Ms. is very worn and damaged.
 The front
                           board originates from a different Ms., it is broken and crudely
                           repaired.
 The back board is missing.
 Remains of a dark brown
                           leather cover (quarter?) have been preserved on the front board.
                           Many fols. are about to fall apart along the ruled lines; many are
                           damaged with the loss of text (s. <locus target="#31">31</locus>, 32);
                           many are missing. 
 <locus target="#33">33</locus> and 34 are
                           detached from the text block and misplaced. 
 ff. 1 and 2 (one
                           bifolia) are of different size and may originate from a different
                           codex.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="2" writtenLines="16">
                           <dimensions unit="mm">
                              <height>85</height>
                              <width>80</width>
                              <dim type="intercolumn">10</dim>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="margin">
                              <dim type="top">10</dim>
                              <dim type="bottom">23</dim>
                              <dim type="right">17</dim>
                              <dim type="left">6</dim>
                              <dim type="intercolumn">10</dim>
                           </dimensions>
                           <note>All data are for <locus target="#10r">10r</locus>.</note>
                           <ab type="ruling">Number differs: from 15 (<locus target="#24r">24r</locus>) to to 17 (<locus target="#12r">12r</locus>).</ab>
                           <ab type="pricking">Pricking and ruling are visible. </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling" subtype="pattern"> Ruling pattern:
                              1A-1A-1A1A/0-0/0-0/C. </ab>
                           <ab type="pricking"> Primary pricks are partly visible. </ab>
                           <ab type="pricking"> Ruling pricks are partly visible. </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The upper line is written above the ruling. </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The bottom line is written above the ruling.</ab>
                        </layout>
                        <layout/>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date>Mid-18th century (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Incipits of sections; elements of the punctuation
                           signs; Ethiopic numerals or their elements.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">On the initial fols., the handwriting
                        is rather fine, regular, with slightly right-sloping, slender letters. From
                           <locus target="#9v">9v</locus> onwards the script tends to broadly spaced
                        and smaller letters and shows more irregularities (cp. <locus target="#27ra">27ra</locus>, 27va-28ra).
                        </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> Some letters have peculiar shapes:
                        </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic"> - መ and ም are often formed with a
                        bigger right loop set on the base line;
                        </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h5" script="Ethiopic"> - ማ, ሚ and ሜ often have the bigger
                        left loop set on the base line, the smaller right loop highly raised;
                        </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h6" script="Ethiopic"> - ሥ, with the 6th order marker very
                        short, aligned to the upper part of the letter (s. <locus target="#5ra">5ra</locus> l.10, 16va l.
                        3,4).</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1va">f. 1va</locus>
                           <desc>: Unidentified text (on the Baptism of Christ in the Jordan River). </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written on a bifolia probably originating from a different codex.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#2ra">f. 2ra</locus>
                           <desc>-b: Unidentified text (fragment from a lectionary?).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written on a bifolia probably originating from a different codex.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- A few corrections written over erasures: e.g., <locus target="#4ra">4ra</locus>, 5ra, 9rb.
 - Erasures marked with thin
                           parallel lines: e.g., <locus target="#3vb">3vb</locus>, 4rb, 12ra;
                           without marking (by secondary hand?): e.g., <locus target="#6ra">6ra</locus>, 10vb, 11va, 20va.
 - Omissions inserted
                           interlineally in secondary hand: e.g., <locus target="#13ra">13ra</locus>.
 - Spaces left for rubricated numerals are left
                           unfilled: e.g., <locus target="#22ra">22ra</locus>, 22va.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="partly">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Two wooden boards (front board re-used, broken and
                           repaired, back board is missing), covered with dark brown leather
                           (possibly quarter, now for the most part missing).
 Two pairs of
                           sewing stations.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                           <material key="leather"/>
                        </decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Endbands"/>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Other"/>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
